captions.text:
- So what do you want
to do after high school?

- Well, I definitely want
to stay in California,

and my first choice
school would be Stanford.
USC is way up on there too!
- What are you going to do after college?
- High School You vs. College You

- Oh no! I can't be late
again or I'll get detention!
- It's 7:58. You've got a couple minutes.
- It is 12:30, sir! You are late!
- Everyone else here is so stupid.

God, I can't wait to
get out of this school.
- (sighs) Everyone else here is so smart.
Asian excellence means nothing in college.
- Guys, got this from my older brother.

- Are you going to eat
all of this for lunch?

- Is that all you're going
to eat for lunch today?
- Yeah, it was like ten cents.
- You can't tell me what to do.
No, you shut up! Okay, whatever. Bye!
- Alright, I'll call you as much as I can.

- I know. She's the
best. I miss her so much.
- Hey, you want to get lunch?

- Do you not want me to
get into a good school?
- Do you want to get lunch?
- (sighs) Why is everyone here so hot?

Jesus! Alright, I'm going
to do some push-ups.

- You know, you are the
only person that gets me.
- Awww, Eugene! Thanks! You're so sweet.

- But it's required
credit. We have to take it.
- I know. But I feel like--
- Did you ever talk to Allison?
- Yeah, I finally talked to her.

- Shut-up! You're like
what? Almost thirty?
- I am not that old, excuse me.
- God, I was suck a dick!
- No, my hair is not that tall.

comments.text:
+xXKarAnimeXx Though it's been a long time since I was in middle school 
(heck, it been a long time since I was in high school), I still have vivid 
memories of middle school. Middle school just wasn't a good time for me. 
It's that awkward phase we all must go through- we aren't kids, we aren't 
adults, we're just trying to figure out what it means to be a teenager. But 
I found high school a lot better. Though I don't miss high school, and 
though I liked college much more, I still had a really good high school 
experience. Enjoy it, because those 4 years go by really quick, even if it 
feels like forever when you're in it. Join a club, or choir, or art class, 
or a sports team and you'll make some great friends!! Hang in there, try to 
enjoy the remaining time in middle school, and pretty soon you'll come into 
yourself and things will get better :)
